                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Mumbai, June 11 (PTI): The Maharashtra government has decided to prosecute television serial producers who have hired child actors to work in their soaps.           
	Last December, the labour ministry had sent showcause notices to these producers under the Child Labour Act and sought information on the child artistes working hours and conditions. But it didnt get a reply.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): Delhi High Court has ordered the government to pay a former All India Radio employee Rs 22 lakh as compensation for becoming permanently disabled after being hit by a government vehicle in 1996. It termed the amount of Rs 6.67 lakh awarded by a lower court as grossly inadequate.                  
	 Chennai (PTI): A US citizen was arrested at a Chennai airport on Thursday after a loaded revolver was found in his baggage. Sellmeyer, 58, claimed he had carried the same weapon when he had flown in from Delhi a fortnight back. He said he was unaware of the fact that carrying firearms on board was an offence in India.                   
	 Mumbai (PTI): Police on Thursday detained 50 members of a union from a Reliance Industries Ltd unit who were on their way to company boss Mukesh Ambanis residence to protest the alleged sacking of some employees. The detainees are members of a union at a Reliance unit in Maharashtras Raigad district.                                                                                                                           
